loc: Osaka Castle Park, Chuo-ku, Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture
rmk:
Suspected ID.  The call resembles that of the black-faced bunting (Emberiza spodocephala),
but the season was too early (and there was no sighting report).
ID based on the comparison with XC356305, XC282641.
The descending pitch favors this ID.
Thrushes are frequently recorded in this place (among leaves on
tall trees).  There was a sighting report of this species in the park
on the same day, but not in this place.
